column6: It seemed to have a better understanding of what was going on.
column8: agreed with most of their responses.  Seemed 'calmer' than blue
column9: It's answers were closer to mine although neither picked the choices in the order I would have.
column11: I tink that one was more like friends and people I have worked with. I feel more confrontable being around that one
column12: For some reason this robot is more memorable to me. I think this robot was correct more often.
column13: BECAUSE THIS ROBOT FAIR THIS TASK
column14: I prefer the red robot because I liked the way they ordered the lists better to a small degree. Maybe I'm biased because I like the color red more than the color blue.
column15: I liked this robot's answers more. This robot seemed more in tune with the situation.
column16: Blue seemed more accurate and less rigid. The blue robot answered the way I would.
column17: To me there is very little difference between the two nor do I agree with either of their answers; however, I think the red bot had a more natural organization for the answers.
column18: It seem like red would answer the questions more correct than the blue
column20: It seemed to have the same choices as myself
column21: I prefer the red robot as it seemed more logical and more rational (especially with questions 4, 5 and 6).   I thought that the blue robot had more emotions and more human-like features but it also felt as if the blue robot wasn't always making the most logical decisions (although I didn't necessarily agree with either robot for questions 1, 2 and 3).   Thus, I would prefer the red robot given the rational decision-making that I observed for questions 4, 5 and 6.
column22: It ordered things more closely to how I would have
column23: I think both were pretty mechanical but at least I thought Red was generally more precise and accurate.
column24: The blue one was more robotic in it's movement and I didn't like that the Red one seemed almost friendly. I would prefer a robot to sound and look robotic than human-like.
column25: I believe that the red robot was simply more coherent in its reasoning than the blue robot was and so I would prefer the one that could at least somewhat mimic person-to-person interaction and not nonsensical conversating.
column27: I like the color better they both seem similar otherwise
column29: I prefer red because it seems like they know how to organize statements or phrases correctly. They have a more natural way of organizing the phrases like a human would.
column30: I feel like it's a little more intelligent is a bit better comprehending certain things over the blue one.
column31: Blue seemed a little better when it came to people, while red seemed better on about situations. So for me the blue would be more of a people oriented robot and better to have around for casual things.
column32: This robot had answer more like what I would have said
column33: Based on it's answers it seems more interesting and I'd like to find out more about it's programming and why it ordered things as it did.
column34: They both were good.  I think the red one was a little more irrational at times which I actually kind of liked.
column35: I liked the order that it ranked things, which usually started with "x or x" instead of just the one "x" statement.
